('19793', '1', 'Mix first 5 ingredients until blended.'),
('19793', '2', 'Brush 1 phyllo sheet lightly with butter; top with 2 more phyllo sheets, lightly brushing each layer with some of the remaining butter.'),
('19793', '3', 'Place remaining phyllo sheet between 2 sheets of plastic wrap until ready to use; set aside.'),
('19793', '4', 'Spread 1/5 of the spinach mixture along one short side of phyllo stack.  Fold in long sides of phyllo; roll up from one short side to make log.  Repeat with remaining phyllo sheets and spinach mixture to make 4 additional logs.'),
('19793', '5', 'Brush with remaining butter.  Make small cuts in tops of logs at 1-inch intervals.'),
('19793', '6', 'Place in large freezer-weight resealable plastic bags or wrap tightly in plastic wrap.'),
('19793', '7', 'Freeze up to 3 months.  When ready to bake, remove desired number of logs from freezer.  Refrigerate, tightly wrapped, several hours or overnight until thawed.  Unwrap, then place on baking sheet.'),
('19793', '8', 'Bake in 375F oven 25 min. or until golden brown.  Cool 5 min.'),
('19793', '9', 'Transfer to cutting board.  Use serrated knife to cut each log into 6 slices.'),
('19797', '1', 'Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat.'),
('19797', '2', 'Add spinach, stewed tomatoes, and garlic, and return mixture to a boil.'),
('19797', '3', 'Stir in tortellini, and cook for 5 minutes. Sprinkle each serving evenly with shredded Parmesan cheese.'),
('19797', '4', 'Note: For testing purposes only, we used Knorr Vegetable Bouillon Cubes.'),
('19799', '1', 'Heat the olive oil in a skillet over medium high heat, and saute the onion until tender. Stir in the tomatoes and spinach, and continue cooking until the spinach is wilted. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in the Roquefort cheese, and allow to melt slightly before serving.'),
('19801', '1', 'Combine all ingredients except dressing in large bowl.'),
('19801', '2', 'Add dressing; mix lightly.'),
('19802', '1', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.'),
('19802', '2', 'Add dressing just before serving; mix lightly.'),
('19809', '1', 'Chop enough mango to measure 1/3 cup; place in blender.'),
('19809', '2', 'Add dressing; blend until smooth.'),
('19809', '3', 'Pour 1/4 cup over chicken in shallow dish; turn to evenly coat both sides of each breast. Refrigerate 30 min. to marinate.'),
('19809', '4', 'Remove chicken from marinade; discard marinade.  Cook chicken in skillet sprayed with cooking spray on medium-high heat 6 to 7 min. on each side or until done (165F).  Cool slightly.  Slice chicken; chop remaining mango.'),
('19809', '5', 'Toss spinach with strawberries, chopped mangos, onions and 1/4 cup of the remaining dressing mixture; spoon onto 4 plates.  Fan 1 chicken breast over each salad.  Top with remaining dressing mixture and nuts.'),
('19810', '1', 'Heat oven to 425F.'),
('19810', '2', 'Mix dressing, honey and rosemary in medium microwavable bowl; brush 1 Tbsp. onto meat in shallow pan.  Set remaining dressing mixture aside.'),
('19810', '3', 'Bake meat 20 to 25 min. or until done (160F).'),
('19810', '4', 'Add apples to remaining dressing mixture; toss to coat.  Microwave on HIGH 1 min. or just until warmed.  Toss with spinach in large bowl.  Slice meat.'),
('19810', '5', 'Add to salad; toss lightly.  Top with cranberries.'),
('19812', '1', 'Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a skillet over medium heat.'),
('19812', '2', 'Add the minced garlic and cook for a couple of minutes. Crank up the heat a bit and throw in the spinach. Stir around and cook for a couple of minutes until the spinach wilts.'),
('19812', '3', 'Remove the spinach from the skillet and put it in a small strainer. Squeeze the excess juice back into the skillet. Set the spinach aside. Throw in the artichokes and cook over medium high heat for several minutes, until liquid is cooked off and artichokes start to get a little color.'),
('19812', '4', 'Remove the artichokes. In the same skillet or a different pot, melt 3 additional tablespoons of butter and whisk in 3 tablespoons of flour until it makes a paste. Cook over medium-low heat for a minute or two, then pour in milk. Stir and cook until slightly thickened; splash in more milk if needed.'),
('19812', '5', 'Add cream cheese, feta, Parmesan, pepper jack, and cayenne and stir until cheese are melted and sauce is smooth. Chop artichokes and spinach and add to the sauce. Stir to combine.'),
('19812', '6', 'Pour into buttered baking dish. Top with extra grated pepper jack and bake at 375 for 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted and bubbly.'),
('19812', '7', 'Serve with pita wedges, chips, or crackers!'),
('19813', '1', 'Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.'),
('19813', '2', 'Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl.'),
('19813', '3', 'Add macaroni; toss lightly.'),
('19814', '1', 'Heat oven to 375F.'),
('19814', '2', 'Mix first 4 ingredients in large bowl until blended.  Stir in 3/4 cup cheddar and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.'),
('19814', '3', 'Spoon into 2-qt. casserole sprayed with cooking spray; top with remaining cracker crumbs and Cheddar.'),
('19814', '4', 'Bake 20 to 25 min. or until heated through.'),
('19815', '1', 'Heat oven to 375F.'),
('19815', '2', 'Mix first 4 ingredients in large bowl until blended.  Stir in 3/4 cup cheddar and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.'),
('19815', '3', 'Spoon into 2-qt. casserole sprayed with cooking spray; top with remaining cracker crumbs and Cheddar.'),
('19815', '4', 'Bake 20 to 25 min. or until heated through.'),
('19819', '1', 'Toss spinach with mushrooms in large bowl.'),
('19819', '2', 'Microwave dressing and bacon in microwaveable bowl on HIGH 15 to 30 sec. or until heated through; stir.'),
('19819', '3', 'Pour over salad; toss to coat.'),
('19820', '1', 'Toss spinach, oranges and bacon bits in large bowl.'),
('19820', '2', 'Add dressing; mix lightly.'),
('19820', '3', 'Serve immediately.'),
