('19826', '2', 'Add dressing; mix lightly.'),
('19826', '3', 'Top with chicken.'),
('19829', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).  Arrange pecans on a single layer on a baking sheet and roast in preheated oven for 7-10 minutes, until they just begin to darken.'),
('19829', '2', 'Remove from oven and set aside.'),
('19829', '3', 'Peel peaches (if desired) and slice into bite-sized segments.'),
('19829', '4', 'Combine peaches, spinach and pecans in a large bowl. Toss with dressing until evenly coated, adding a little additional dressing, if necessary.'),
('19830', '1', 'Cook bacon in small saucepan until crisp.'),
('19830', '2', 'Remove bacon from saucepan, reserving 1 Tbsp. drippings in pan.'),
('19830', '3', 'Drain bacon on paper towels.  Stir dressing into reserved drippings.'),
('19830', '4', 'Toss spinach with bacon and tomatoes in large bowl.'),
('19830', '5', 'Add dressing mixture and cheese; mix lightly.'),
('19839', '1', 'Put spinach in a large microwave-safe bowl and drape bowl with microwave-safe plastic wrap. Microwave until spinach is tender, stirring a couple of times, 4 to 5 minutes.'),
('19839', '2', 'Drain spinach and let stand until cool enough to handle. Squeeze out liquid, then finely chop.'),
('19839', '3', 'Whirl cottage cheese, parmesan, salt, and pepper in a food processor until very smooth, about 1 minute, scraping inside of bowl as needed.'),
('19839', '4', 'Scrape into a bowl and stir in spinach.'),
('19839', '5', 'Serve dip at room temperature or chilled, with baguette toasts or crackers.'),
('19839', '6', 'Make ahead: Up to 2 days, chilled.'),
('19840', '1', 'Combine pears, chicken and dressing in large bowl.'),
('19840', '2', 'Add spinach; mix lightly.'),
('19840', '3', 'Serve immediately.'),
('19843', '1', 'Build a fire in your grill.'),
('19843', '2', 'In a large saucepan, bring the white vinegar, bay leaf, and enough water to cover the sweetbreads to a boil over high heat.'),
('19843', '3', 'Add the sweetbreads and salt and pepper, lower the heat so that the water just barely simmers, and poach gently for 10 minutes; drain and place the sweetbreads in a bowl of ice water to cool.'),
('19843', '4', 'When the sweetbreads are completely cooled, drain them, dry them with paper towels, and remove as much of the membrane as possible. Separate the meat into nuggets, toss them gently with  cup of the olive oil, and sprinkle generously with salt and pepper. Thread the sweetbreads onto four to six skewers (one per serving) and refrigerate.'),
('19843', '5', 'Place the spinach in a large bowl. In a large saut pan, cook the bacon slowly over medium heat until it is crisp and golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('19843', '6', 'Drain off and discard all but 3 tablespoons of the fat, leaving the bacon in the pan.'),
('19843', '7', 'Add the sugar, the remaining  cup olive oil, and the balsamic vinegar to the pan and bring to a boil.'),
('19843', '8', 'Pour the hot dressing over the spinach, tossing to wilt the spinach and coat it with the dressing. Season with salt and pepper and set aside.'),
('19843', '9', 'When the fire has died down and the coals are medium-hot (you can hold your hand 5 inches above the surface of the grill for 3 to 4 seconds), place the skewers on the grill and cook until well seared and crisp on the outside, 4 to 5 minutes per side. To check for doneness, nick, peek, and cheat: Make a -inch cut in the thickest part of one of the nuggets; it should be warm throughout with no red, only the faintest trace of pink. When the sweetbreads are fully cooked, remove them from the heat and let them rest for 5 minutes.'),
('19843', '10', 'To serve, place some spinach on each plate and top with a sweetbread skewer.'),
