('19846', '1', 'Toss spinach, chicken, broccoli and tomatoes in large bowl.'),
('19846', '2', 'Add dressing; mix lightly.'),
('19851', '1', 'In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat.  Stir in shallots and cook until transparent, about 5 minutes.'),
('19851', '2', 'Add spinach, sprinkle with salt and pepper; cook and stir 3 to 5 minutes until leaves are wilted and reduced.'),
('19881', '1', 'In a large bowl, cover peas with 4 inches of water and soak a minimum of 6 hours, or overnight.'),
('19881', '2', 'Drain and rinse thoroughly.'),
('19881', '3', 'Place peas in a 4-quart saucepan with chicken broth or water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer peas between 45 to 55 minutes, or until peas are cooked but not mushy.'),
('19881', '4', 'Drain excess liquid and let peas cool to room temperature.'),
('19881', '5', 'Combine buttermilk, mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, hot sauce salt and pepper in a bowl, and whisk to incorporate.'),
('19881', '6', 'In a salad bowl, combine beans, red onion, celery and chives.'),
('19881', '7', 'Pour dressing over bean mixture and gently stir to incorporate, being careful not to break up too many of the beans.'),
('19881', '8', 'Add spinach and toss to coat. Season with additional salt, pepper and hot sauce, to taste.'),
('19881', '9', 'Serve immediately.'),
('19882', '1', 'Bring a pot of lightly salted water to a boil.'),
('19882', '2', 'Add orzo pasta, cook for 5 minutes, or until al dente.'),
('19882', '3', 'Drain.'),
('19882', '4', 'Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.'),
('19882', '5', 'Place the lamb and garlic in the skillet. Season lamb with coriander, salt, and pepper. Cook until evenly browned.'),
('19882', '6', 'Remove from heat, and drain.'),
('19882', '7', 'In a large bowl, mix the spinach, tomatoes, lemon juice and zest, mint, parsley, green onions, and remaining olive oil. Toss with the orzo, lamb, and feta cheese to serve.'),
('19895', '1', 'Heat the oil in a very large pot over medium heat.'),
('19895', '2', 'Add the onion and garlic, and saute until tender, about 8 minutes.'),
('19895', '3', 'Add 1/3 of the spinach and saute until it begins to wilt, about 1 to 2 minutes. Continue adding the spinach 1 handful at a time, sauteing just until it begins to wilt before adding more.'),
('19895', '4', 'Add the soy sauce and crushed red pepper.'),
('19895', '5', 'Saute over high heat until spinach wilts. Season the mixture, to taste, with salt and black pepper.'),
('19895', '6', 'Transfer the mixture to a bowl and serve.'),
('19917', '1', 'Pour 1/4 cup dressing over chicken in shallow glass dish; turn chicken to evenly coat both sides of each breast. Refrigerate 30 min. to marinate.'),
('19917', '2', 'Heat grill to medium heat.'),
('19917', '3', 'Remove chicken from marinade; discard marinade. Grill chicken 6 to 8 min. on each side or until done (165F); cut into strips.'),
('19917', '4', 'Place chicken and vegetables on spinach-covered platter; sprinkle with nuts.'),
('19917', '5', 'Drizzle with remaining dressing.'),
('19918', '1', 'Mix dressing, honey, lemon juice and basil.'),
('19918', '2', 'Remove 1/2 cup of the dressing mixture for later use.'),
('19918', '3', 'Place chicken on greased rack of broiler pan; brush with remaining dressing mixture.'),
('19918', '4', 'Broil 10 min.  Turn chicken over; broil an additional 7 to 10 min. or until chicken is cooked through (170F).'),
('19918', '5', 'Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces; cover to keep warm.'),
('19918', '6', 'Toss spinach with mushrooms; top with chicken.'),
('19918', '7', 'Drizzle with reserved 1/2 cup dressing mixture just before serving.'),
('19919', '1', 'Combine bacon, dressing and water in small microwaveable bowl.  Microwave on HIGH 30 sec. or until heated through.'),
('19919', '2', 'Toss spinach with chicken, onions and mushrooms in medium bowl.'),
('19919', '3', 'Add dressing mixture; mix lightly.'),
('19919', '4', 'Serve warm.'),
('19920', '1', 'Pour the oil into a large pot and turn the heat to medium.'),
('19920', '2', 'Add the onion and carrot and cook until the onion is soft.'),
('19920', '3', 'Add the garlic and cook for another minute.'),
('19920', '4', 'Pour in the chicken stock into the pot and bring to a simmer.  Dump in the spinach and parsley and cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.'),
('19920', '5', 'Meanwhile, fill a very large bowl with some ice.  Set a smaller bowl on top that is still big enough to hold the liquid from the soup.  When the soup is done, strain the soup through a metal strainer into the smaller bowl sitting on top of the ice.  Cool the soup completely.'),
('19920', '6', 'When ready to serve, return the strained soup to a pot and bring to a simmer.  Ladle into bowls, and sprinkle a little tarragon on top and dollop with sour cream.  Season with salt and pepper to taste.'),
('19921', '1', 'Melt butter in large saucepan on medium-high heat.'),
('19921', '2', 'Add onions and garlic; cook and stir until onions are crisp-tender.  Stir in wine; simmer 5 min., stirring occasionally.'),
('19921', '3', 'Add flour; mix well.  Gradually add milk, stirring until well blended.  Cook until mixture thickens and begins to boil, stirring constantly.  Boil 1 min.'),
('19921', '4', 'Stir in remaining ingredients; cook until heated through, stirring occasionally.'),
('19933', '1', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('19933', '2', 'Add onion, ginger, and garlic; saut 4 minutes or until mixture begins to brown.'),
('19933', '3', 'Add water and tomato paste; cook 2 minutes or until liquid evaporates, stirring constantly. Stir in spinach, chili powder, salt, and chickpeas; cover. Reduce heat; cook 5 minutes or until spinach wilts and mixture is heated. Stir in juice.'),
('19933', '4', 'Serve over rice.'),
('19933', '5', 'Garnish with lemon wedges and rind, if desired.'),
('19936', '1', 'In a bowl, cover the bulgur with warm tap water.'),
('19936', '2', 'Let stand until the grains are tender, about 2 hours.'),
('19936', '3', 'Drain the bulgur well.'),
('19936', '4', 'In a large bowl, whisk the lemon zest with the lemon juice and chopped dill.'),
('19936', '5', 'Whisk in the olive oil.'),
('19936', '6', 'Add the bulgur, shrimp, baby spinach, sliced radishes and pine nuts and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper and serve.'),
('19938', '1', 'Melt the remaining 2 tablespoons butter in a skillet over medium heat.'),
('19938', '2', 'Add the shallots or onions and cook until softened, about 3 minutes. Stir in the spinach, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and a pinch of pepper. Cook until the spinach is heated through, about 2 minutes.'),
('19938', '3', 'Grease an 8-inch-square baking dish with butter. (I used an 8 x 11 inch baking dish and filled it up completely, but it had short sides--only about an inch.) Arrange half of the bread, buttered-side up, in a single layer in the dish. Scatter half of the spinach mixture and 1/2 cup of the cheese over the bread. Repeat, making another layer of bread, spinach, and cheese.'),
('19938', '4', 'Whisk together the eggs, half-and-half, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper until smooth.'),
('19938', '5', 'Pour this mixture evenly over the top of the layered bread, spinach, and cheese. Cover the surface with plastic wrap and put a 2-pound bag of sugar on top to weigh it down. Refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.'),
('19938', '6', 'Preheat the oven to 325 degrees. Allow the strata to stand at room temperature for 20 minutes before baking. When ready to bake, remove the sugar weight, remove the plastic wrap, and sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup cheese over the top.'),
('19938', '7', 'Bake until both the edges and center are puffed and the edges have pulled away slightly from the sides of the dish, 50 to 55 minutes. (The center of my strata never really puffed, so I removed it when the edges pulled away from the sides of the dish.) Cool on a wire rack 5 minutes before serving.'),
('19940', '1', 'Toss spinach with chicken, tomatoes and cucumber in large bowl.'),
('19940', '2', 'Add dressing; mix lightly.'),
('19940', '3', 'Sprinkle with cheese.'),
('19941', '1', 'Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.'),
('19941', '2', 'Add mushrooms and garlic; cook and stir 3 to 5 min. or until mushrooms are tender.'),
('19941', '3', 'Add spinach; cook and stir on medium heat 4 to 5 min. or just until spinach is wilted.'),
('19941', '4', 'Stir in pepper; sprinkle with cheese.'),
('19961', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('19961', '2', 'Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F. Melt the butter in a heavy-bottomed saute pan over medium heat.'),
('19961', '3', 'Add the onions and saute until translucent, about 15 minutes.'),
('19961', '4', 'Add the flour and nutmeg and cook, stirring, for 2 more minutes.'),
('19961', '5', 'Add the cream and milk and cook until thickened. Squeeze as much liquid as possible from the spinach and add the spinach to the sauce.'),
('19961', '6', 'Add 1/2 cup of the Parmesan cheese and mix well. Season, to taste, with salt and pepper.'),
('19961', '7', 'Transfer the spinach to a baking dish and sprinkle the remaining 1/2 cup Parmesan and the Gruyere on top.'),
('19961', '8', 'Bake for 20 minutes until hot and bubbly.'),
('19961', '9', 'Serve hot.'),
('19961', '10', 'Note: This recipe has been updated and may differ from what was originally broadcast or published.'),
('19966', '1', 'Combine all ingredients in a serving bowl. Salt to taste.'),
('19967', '1', 'Cook ribs in half the dressing in large deep skillet or Dutch oven on medium-high heat 4 min. on each side or until browned on both sides.'),
('19967', '2', 'Remove ribs from skillet; cover to keep warm.'),
('19967', '3', 'Combine remaining  dressing and cubed pork in skillet; cook and stir 4 min. or until pork is evenly browned on both sides.'),
('19967', '4', 'Remove pork from skillet; cover to keep warm.  Stir in onions; cook and stir 5 min.'),
('19967', '5', 'Add ribs, pork loin, salsa and water; cover.  Simmer on medium-low 1 hour.'),
('19967', '6', 'Add purslane and ham; cook, covered, 15 min. or until rib meat is tender.'),
('19970', '1', 'In a large saucepan, heat the 2 tablespoons of olive oil.'),
('19970', '2', 'Add the onion and garlic and cook over moderate heat until translucent, about 8 minutes. Stir in the thyme and bay leaf and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.'),
('19970', '3', 'Add the sliced zucchini, season with salt and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 10 minutes.'),
('19970', '4', 'Add the water and bring to a boil.'),
('19970', '5', 'Remove the saucepan from the heat. Discard the bay leaf and stir in the shredded basil.'),
('19970', '6', 'Working in batches, puree the soup in a blender until very smooth.'),
('19970', '7', 'Transfer the zucchini puree to a large bowl. Stir in the ice. Refrigerate the zucchini soup for at least 3 hours, until thoroughly chilled.'),
('19970', '8', 'Season the soup with salt and pepper. Ladle into shallow bowls and top with a small handful of purslane and zucchini shavings.'),
('19970', '9', 'Drizzle with olive oil and serve.'),
('19972', '1', '1 pound raclette, thinly sliced'),
('19972', '2', 'Purslane, for garnish'),
('19973', '1', 'Cut peel, including white pith, from lemon with a small sharp knife. Working over a bowl to catch juices, cut lemon segments free from membranes, letting segments drop into bowl.'),
('19973', '2', 'Crush lemongrass stalk with side of a heavy knife (to release oils), then thinly slice. Bring stock, lemongrass, and chile to a boil in a 1- to 1 1/2-quart heavy saucepan. Cover pan and remove from heat, then let stand 20 minutes.'),
('19973', '3', 'Return to a boil and add lemon segments with juice and lime leaves. Cover pan and remove from heat, then let stand 20 minutes more.'),
('19973', '4', 'Pour mixture through a fine-mesh sieve into a small bowl, discarding solids, then return to saucepan and whisk in oil. Bring vinaigrette to a boil and whisk in cornstarch mixture, then simmer, whisking occasionally, 2 minutes. Cool completely.'),
('19973', '5', 'Whisk in herbs and salt and pepper to taste.'),
('19974', '1', 'Whisk together oil, lemon juice, shallot, and 1/4 teaspoon each of salt and pepper in a large bowl.'),
('19974', '2', 'Add tomatoes, purslane, and parsley, gently tossing to coat.'),
('19975', '1', 'Heat oil in a large (not nonstick) frying pan over medium-high heat. Season pork chops on both sides with 1/4 tsp. each salt and pepper and brown on both sides, 5 minutes total.'),
('19975', '2', 'Transfer chops to a plate.'),
('19975', '3', 'Add onion and chiles to pan, reduce heat to medium, and cook, covered, until onion softens, about 10 minutes. Stir in tomatoes, garlic, and oregano and cook 5 minutes more, covered.'),
('19975', '4', 'Nestle pork chops into tomatoes and onion and add 1 1/2 cups purslane. Cover and cook 7 minutes, stir in remaining purslane, and cook just until slightly wilted, about 3 minutes more. Stir in lemon zest, juice, remaining 1/4 tsp. salt, and pepper to taste.'),
('19977', '1', 'Rinse the black-eyed peas and chickpeas.'),
('19977', '2', 'Pour them into separate medium saucepans and cover with several inches of water. Cover and cook over moderate heat until tender, about 20 minutes for the black-eyed peas and 1 hour for the chickpeas.'),
('19977', '3', 'Drain the black-eyed peas and discard the liquid.'),
('19977', '4', 'Drain the chickpeas; reserve 1/3 cup of the cooking liquid.'),
('19977', '5', 'Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, combine the lentils with 4 cups of water, cover partially and cook over moderate heat until tender, about 40 minutes.'),
('19977', '6', 'Drain; reserve 2 cups of the cooking liquid.'),
('19977', '7', 'In a large, enameled cast-iron casserole, heat 2 tablespoons of the oil.'),
('19977', '8', 'Add the lamb and cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until browned, about 5 minutes. Stir in the onion, cover and cook until softened but not browned, about 2 minutes.'),
('19977', '9', 'Add the tomato paste, red pepper paste and 1/2 cup of water and bring to a simmer. Cover and cook, stirring once or twice, until the mixture begins to caramelize, about 20 minutes.'),
('19977', '10', 'Add the purslane, bulgur and the reserved chickpea and lentil cooking liquids to the casserole. Cover and cook for 10 minutes.'),
('19977', '11', 'Add the chickpeas, black-eyed peas, lentils, garlic and enough water to barely cover. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.'),
('19977', '12', 'Remove from the heat, stir in the lemon juice and season with salt.'),
('19977', '13', 'In a small skillet, heat the remaining 2 tablespoons of oil.'),
('19977', '14', 'Add the spearmint, Turkish red pepper flakes and 1/4 teaspoon ground black pepper. When the oil begins to sizzle, give it a stir and drizzle it over the stew. Stir once and let stand for 30 minutes.'),
('19977', '15', 'Serve the stew at room temperature or let cool, then refrigerate and serve chilled the following day. Pass the scallions and lemon at the table.'),
('19980', '1', 'Prepare a grill for medium heat (350 to 450). If using charcoal, add chips or wood chunks evenly over coals. If using gas, put chips or chunks in a shallow foil pan set on burner in corner of grill. Grill chiles, tomatoes, and onions, turning often, until skins blacken all over, 15 to 20 minutes.'),
('19980', '2', 'Let vegetables cool, then peel. Stem and seed chiles. Chop vegetables and put in a medium pot with artichokes, herbs, purslane, vinegar, and 1/2 tsp. salt; bring to a boil, then cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until onions soften, 20 to 30 minutes.'),
('19980', '3', 'Remove from heat; let sit 1 hour, covered, so flavors can marry.'),
('19980', '4', 'Pure roughly in a food processor, thinning with hot water to make it pourable.'),
('19980', '5', 'Let cool and season with salt to taste.'),
('19980', '6', 'Serve with oysters.'),
('19980', '7', '*Find red oak chips online from Susie Q''s Brand (susieqbrand.com).'),
('19983', '1', 'Cook chiles in large skillet 5 min. or until toasted, stirring frequently.'),
('19983', '2', 'Place in blender.'),
('19983', '3', 'Add garlic, tomatillos and onions to skillet; cook 10 min. or until roasted, stirring frequently.  Peel garlic and add to blender with tomatillas and onions; blend until smooth.'),
('19983', '4', 'Cook meat in 6-qt. pressure cooker on medium-high heat 4 min. on each side or until browned on both sides; top with tomatillo sauce. LOCK pressure cooker lid in place. Cook on medium-high heat until pressure vent locks in place and regulator begins to rock gently. Reduce heat gradually to maintain slow steady rocking motion; cook 40 to 45 min. or until meat is tender.'),
('19983', '5', 'Remove from heat.'),
('19983', '6', 'Let stand 10 min. or until pressure vent drops.'),
('19983', '7', 'Remove regulator, then lid; stir in purslane.  Replace lid.'),
('19983', '8', 'Let stand 5 min. or until purslane is wilted.'),
('19983', '9', 'Meanwhile, bring water, broth and hominy to boil in saucepan; cover.  Simmer on low heat 55 min. or until hominy is softened and liquid is absorbed.'),
('19983', '10', 'Transfer to serving bowl; top with cheese.'),
('19983', '11', 'Serve topped with meat mixture and pork rinds.'),
('19984', '1', 'Cut peel, including all white pith, from lemon with a sharp paring knife. Working over a bowl, cut segments from half of lemon free from membranes and transfer segments to a cutting board, then squeeze juice from membranes and remaining 1/2 lemon into bowl.'),
('19984', '2', 'Transfer 2 tablespoons juice to a large bowl, then finely chop segments and add to measured juice.'),
('19984', '3', 'Add salt, pepper, and oil, whisking to combine, then stir in remaining ingredients.'),
('19985', '1', 'Preheat oven to 375°F.'),
('19985', '2', 'Split pita loaves and toast on a baking sheet in middle of oven until golden, 10 to 15 minutes. Cool pitas on a rack and break into bite-size pieces.'),
('19985', '3', 'While pitas are toasting, whisk together lemon juice, pomegranate molasses, and salt to taste in a serving bowl, then whisk in oil until emulsified.'),
('19985', '4', 'Add pitas to dressing with remaining ingredients and toss to combine.'),
